text: I recommend this film to anybody who likes being scared or creeped out! As a horror fan, not a lot of films creep me out. So far the best horror film of the year! If you were a fan of The Conjuring, you'll be a bigger fan I of this! And just clearing this up, this is a film on its own. Not apart of the conjuring franchise, but its related to it. Like a cousin almost. This Conjuring 2 is titled The Conjuring 2: The Enfield Poltergeist which is based on a true story, and one the most popular supernatural cases in the world. Anyways, I give this film 5/5! Great film!

text: Ghostbusters II moment at 2:03  I saw this trailer yesterday - oh dear. What a mess. The film looks like a low rent, rent once tv movie. Then I find out now it's a true prequel to the Conjuring, which will surely disappoint many! If I had known it was a prequel, would I have accepted it more? I don't know. I doubt it.Â Doll related horror movies have been done far too many times too, so unless you havent watched muched horror other than modern, this is nothing new and more of a hopeful cash cow.Â   The 'scary moment' screams, sounds, and flash effects, being grabbed and dragged along the floor-nothing new. The whispering at the start trying to be scary is slightly laughable. The doll didn't even blink or twitch once to give more of a hint as to what it was about.Â On the plus side, the cut down version of the trailer on here is slightly better.

text: Iâ€™m a horror movie fan â€“ Iâ€™m a fan of the original evil dead trilogy to Romero to Poltergeist, korean horror, french horror etcâ€¦ Iâ€™m also a fan of the new wave of horror. Iâ€™m a fan of the Conjuring as it was a film that made me think the art of a horror movie is back. First offâ€¦ this isnâ€™t made by James Wanâ€¦ itâ€™s made by itâ€™s filmographer so off of the bat youâ€™re probably going to get some cool scenes but perhaps lack of character development. The budget of Annabelle is $5 million (thatâ€™s 1/4 of what the Conjuring cost). Let me tell you the script is the weakest part of this film. The movie starts off slowâ€¦ this is where the film should really get you into the characters but there isnâ€™t much here, itâ€™s generic. Itâ€™s the weakest part of the film. You have your standard coupleâ€¦ man goes to work, woman stays home and experiences weird stuff. The problem with this is that itâ€™s hard for you to bother to relate to the characters. This kind of kills the film for me. There were actually a lot that could have been explored but they didnâ€™t touch like the kids in the apartment. Now the good. There is very little CGI â€“ perhaps none. Itâ€™s all old school. This is something that anyone could actually filmâ€¦. chair moving, oven is on, someone standing there. Itâ€™s good. It works. Thereâ€™s a great scene here with a baby. Are there enough scares? Not really. The pay off for the film felt like they might have fixed the movie for censors but even though the film is Rated R. Thereâ€™s a lot missing in this film. Itâ€™s not horrible. Itâ€™s worth a rental. Itâ€™s your average horror movie.
